And staying with the plight of the needy and bright, it is reprieve for a 13-year-old girl whose dreams to pursue secondary school education were almost dashing due to lack of school fees. Naomy kwamboka who scored 335 marks in her KCPE examination has been camping at central police station in Nakuru for three days now instead of being at AIC Morop girls  before a good well wisher  came to her rescue.